JOHANNESBURG – Two men who escaped from the Johannesburg Correctional Centre have been shot dead in KwaZulu-Natal. They were two of 16 men who escaped from the Johannesburg prison, also known as Sun City in the early hours of Monday. READ: At least 20 killed in Brazil prison breakout bid: officials The men were shot dead on Tuesday night near Greytown after they exchanged fire with the police. On Monday, police said they were investigating the Johannesburg Correctional Centre for any loopholes that may have aided the break-out.  eNCA